The paper discusses the problem of one-class classification, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper presents a taxonomy of study for OCC problems based on the availability of training data, algorithms used, and application domains applied. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DM (Data Mining), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these sub-categories are relevant to the problem of OCC and its applications.
